{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775852677012,"sessionID":"ses_286efe104ffee5TgU7J0piu7fM","part":{"id":"prt_d7911678e001J0RxbhViTEZW7K","messageID":"msg_d79115fbf0010lwf4dX2QXXF2m","sessionID":"ses_286efe104ffee5TgU7J0piu7fM","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852749946,"sessionID":"ses_286efe104ffee5TgU7J0piu7fM","part":{"id":"prt_d79116a4b001Zy2rbtOUVcaj4U","messageID":"msg_d79115fbf0010lwf4dX2QXXF2m","sessionID":"ses_286efe104ffee5TgU7J0piu7fM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_fb4e64641b0a4b0c960839d8","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification — AR-012: Session Store Interface\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** New feature — Session persistence layer for sandbox orchestration\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-001: Store Interface Contract\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface implemented by Redis\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=redis`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `Store` is `*redisStore` implementing all 9 methods\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface implemented by Valkey\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `Store` is `*valkeyStore` implementing all 9 methods\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Not Found Semantics\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` runs\n- **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `redis.Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n\n#### Scenario: Update last-activity on missing session\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, time.Now())` is called\n- **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Session Key Naming\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n\n#### Scenario: Key construction\n- **GIVEN** session id `abc-123`\n- **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n- **THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Expiry Index (Sorted Set)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n- **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1000, 0)`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` succeeds\n- **THEN** `session:expiry` contains member `sandbox.SessionID` with score `1000`\n\n#### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n- **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n- **THEN** it selects members with scores from `-inf` through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from expiry index\n- **GIVEN** session `abc` exists in `session:expiry` ZSET\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` succeeds\n- **THEN** `session:expiry` no longer contains member `abc`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Last-Activity Index (Sorted Set)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox initializes last-activity\n- **GIVEN** a new sandbox being stored at time `T`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` succeeds\n- **THEN** `session:last_activity` contains member `sandbox.SessionID` with score `T.Unix()`\n\n#### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n- **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n- **WHEN** executed\n- **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity bumps timestamp\n- **GIVEN** session `abc` with last-activity score `1000`\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Unix(2000, 0))` succeeds\n- **THEN** `session:last_activity` member `abc` has score `2000`\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from activity index\n- **GIVEN** session `abc` exists in `session:last_activity` ZSET\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` succeeds\n- **THEN** `session:last_activity` no longer contains member `abc`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: StoreSandbox Atomicity and Validation\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n\n#### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n- **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil (no backend operation)\n\n#### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero value)\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error indicates ExpiresAt is invalid (no backend operation)\n\n#### Scenario: Duplicate store fails (SETNX)\n- **GIVEN** session `abc` already exists in backend\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with same `SessionID` is called\n- **THEN** operation fails (SETNX returns 0)\n\n#### Scenario: Pipeline atomicity\n- **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with valid data\n- **WHEN** pipeline executes SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity\n- **THEN** all three succeed or all fail; no partial writes\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n\n#### Scenario: Update existing session\n- **GIVEN** session `abc` exists with JSON value V1\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with updated data succeeds\n- **THEN** JSON value is V2; `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` unchanged\n\n#### Scenario: Missing key on update\n- **GIVEN** session key `session:abc` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` runs\n- **THEN** Redis: `SETXX` returns false → error; Valkey: response not `\"OK\"` → error\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n\n#### Scenario: Full removal\n- **GIVEN** an existing session in main key + both ZSETs\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` succeeds\n- **THEN** GET `session:{id}` returns not found AND both ZSETs no longer contain the member\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: List Loaders Tolerate Missing Keys\n\n**Requirement:** When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing without failing the whole batch.\n\n#### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n- **GIVEN** a session id in `session:expiry` ZSET without a string value\n- **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, ids)` runs\n- **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice (no error)\n\n#### Scenario: Partial MGET success\n- **GIVEN** 5 session ids in ZSET; 3 have string values, 2 are orphaned\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 10)` runs\n- **THEN** returns slice of 3 sandboxes (orphans skipped silently)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n\n#### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n- **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", time.Now())`\n- **WHEN** called\n- **THEN** error indicates session id is empty\n\n#### Scenario: Zero time uses Now\n- **GIVEN** session `abc` exists; `at = time.Time{}`\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Time{})` is called\n- **THEN** ZADD uses `time.Now().Unix()` as score\n\n#### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n- **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, time.Now())` is called\n- **THEN** return `ErrNotFound` (no ZADD performed)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: Provider Selection via STORE_TYPE\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n\n#### Scenario: Default redis\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n- **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Case-insensitive store type\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=REDIS` or `STORE_TYPE=Redis`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey selected\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid store type fails\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=memcached`\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: Redis Environment and Password Policy\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n\n#### Scenario: Password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n\n#### Scenario: Password disabled explicitly\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** connection proceeds with empty password\n\n#### Scenario: Password provided\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` both set\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** connection uses provided password\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: Valkey Environment and Options\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n\n#### Scenario: Comma-separated addresses\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=node1:6379,node2:6379,node3:6379`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `InitAddress` contains three addresses\n\n#### Scenario: Optional client flags — DisableCache\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n\n#### Scenario: Optional client flags — ForceSingle\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is true on `ClientOption`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid boolean falls back to false\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=maybe`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `DisableCache` is false (ParseBool fails)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Singleton Access\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n\n#### Scenario: Single initialization\n- **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently\n- **WHEN** they run at the same time\n- **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n\n#### Scenario: Fatal on init failure\n- **GIVEN** invalid configuration (e.g., missing `REDIS_ADDR`)\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n- **THEN** klog.Fatalf is invoked with error message\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n### SandboxInfo (from `pkg/common/types`)\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n    SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n    Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n    EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns\n\n| Component | Pattern |\n|-----------|---------|\n| Session document | `session:{sessionID}` |\n| Expiry index | `session:expiry` (ZSET: member=sessionID, score=ExpiresAt.Unix()) |\n| Last-activity index | `session:last_activity` (ZSET: member=sessionID, score=LastActivity.Unix()) |\n\n---\n\n## Error Definitions\n\n```go\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Case-insensitive; `redis` or `valkey` |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes (if redis) | — | Redis server address |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless disabled | — | Empty allowed if `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive; set to `false` to allow empty password |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes (if valkey) | — | Comma-separated addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless disabled | — | Empty allowed if `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | ParseBool; enables `DisableCache` if true |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | ParseBool; enables `ForceSingleClient` if true |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Redis Client\n- Library: `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n- Type: `*redisv9.Client`\n- Pipeline: Used for `StoreSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n\n### Valkey Client\n- Library: `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n- Type: `valkey.Client`\n- MGET: Used in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` (requires same slot deployment consideration)\n\n### Zero-Limit Handling\n- `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `pkg/store/store.go` — Store interface with 9 methods + `ErrNotFound`\n- [ ] `pkg/store/singleton.go` — `Storage()`, `initStore()`, provider constants\n- [ ] `pkg/store/store_redis.go` — Redis implementation with pipeline operations\n- [ ] `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` — Valkey implementation with DoMulti operations\n- [ ] `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — `SandboxInfo`, `SandboxEntryPoint` types\n- [ ] Unit tests for all 14 requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n- [ ] Integration tests with real Redis and Valkey instances\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775852749934,"end":1775852749942}}}}
